# No Fee Percentages on Landing

Marketing and landing surfaces must not mention platform fee or winner payout percentages (for example `25%`, `75%`, `25 %`, `75 %`).

## Surfaces this covers

- `Bobeta.Landing/**` (pages, components, `HelpCopy`, FAQ, terms, rules, privacy, responsible play)
- Landing i18n keys (`landing_*`) in `I18nService`
- Hero, trust chips, feature cards, ticker, footer, FAQ answers, legal/help blurbs written for the public site

## What to write instead

- Say the idea without the number: platform fee, winners paid to wallet, instant payouts, cash out to MoMo.
- Keep exact splits for in-app stake and wallet UI only (`potential_win`, `platform_fee`, create-game summaries, and similar).

## Examples

```text
Bad: 75% winner payout
Good: Winners paid instantly

Bad: Bobeta takes a platform fee (25%). The rest goes to the winner.
Good: Bobeta takes a platform fee. The rest goes to the winner.

Bad: Winners receive 75% of the pot straight to their wallet.
Good: Win, then get paid straight to your wallet.
```

## When editing

- Do not reintroduce percentages while translating or expanding landing/help copy.
- If a percent is required for honesty, put it only on authenticated stake or wallet screens, not on `/` or public help/legal pages.
